(149, 1, '2012-12-18 05:58:09', '2012-12-18 05:58:09', '<span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">Interactive marketing agency The Creative Shop has appointed two business directors to replace its outgoing CEO Mark Bailey. David Wommelsdorff has been promoted to director - business development and Marcus Joy to director - project implementation. The two have been responsible for spearheading the direction of the company over the past 12 months, during which time the agency has won projects for Nokia, Bupa, Fisher &amp; Paykel, Nike, Jack Daniels – Japan, Olay and the City of Melbourne. </span>', 'NEWS IN BRIEF: WEDNESDAY 22 AUGUST', 'Interactive marketing agency The Creative Shop has appointed two business directors to replace its outgoing CEO Mark Bailey. David Wommelsdorff has been promoted to director - business development and Marcus Joy to director - project implementation. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'news-in-brief-wednesday-22-august', '', '', '2012-12-18 06:11:52', '2012-12-18 06:11:52', '', 0, 'http://192.168.204.156/wordpress/?post_type=news&#038;p=149', 0, 'news', '', 0),
