(68, 1, '2012-12-14 04:05:16', '2012-12-14 04:05:16', 'Daniel is the Director of The Creative Shop (TCS), focusing on growing the company’s business globally. Before joining TCS, Daniel managed ‘Ipartners’ - the largest digital agency in Korea as well as managing Digital Insight Korea which is a conference and a knowledge service provider for the IT industry. During this time, he successfully provided consulting services to Samsung Electronics, Sony, LG Electronics, Coca-Cola, Canon, Johnson&amp;Johnson and developing successful case studies.\r\n\r\nBy joining TCS, Daniel has established a cooperative relationship with Korean partners who are world leaders in the IT industry. This enables TCS to provide innovative marketing solution to their clients in Australia.\r\n\r\nDaniel completed his undergraduate studies of Business management from DanKook University, Korea and an MBA from same University. Daniel has participated as Speakers at small to large conferences and seminars and has won many awards such as Korea Digital Media Festival Award, Web Award Korea and International Business Awards.\r\n\r\n"In recent years, there has been a rapid increase in the evolution of Interactive (Digital) marketing especially with the growth of the social media paradigm and the introduction of new media platforms such as Smartphone, Tablet PC and Digital signage. The risk of marketing falling behind, generation 2.0 of the digital phenomena is very real.\r\nHowever, companies, which can approach this challenge with new strategies and accurately read the changes of the industry, will have an advantage. TCS has a unique depth of experience to be the perfect partner for companies who want to successfully surf above the digital evolution wave helping to alleviate the fear of the ever evolving digital environment. If you are looking for the best marketing partner to create better business opportunities in the new digital environment, talk to The Creative Shop today."', 'Daniel Hugh', 'By joining TCS, Daniel has established a cooperative relationship with Korean partners who are world leaders in the IT industry. This enables TCS to provide innovative marketing solution to their clients in Australia. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'daniel-hugh', '', '', '2012-12-14 04:05:16', '2012-12-14 04:05:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=director&#038;p=68', 0, 'director', '', 0),
(69, 1, '2012-12-14 04:07:12', '2012-12-14 04:07:12', 'KevinBae’s demonstrated business success in Australia and overseas and his leading corporate advisory roles are added dimensions to an already heightened status he holds in Australia generally and our local community more specifically.\r\n\r\nKevin Bae has been a Chartered Accountant since 1996 and is currently Chairman of The Creative Shop (TCS), focusing on providing strategic business insights and driving the long term vision of the company.\r\n\r\nHe has previously been involved as a Partner for over 20 years in a significant multi-national Sydney based Chartered Accounting firm with a firmly established reputation for providing a range of tax and advisory services to Australian companies and foreign enterprises, particularly from China and Korea. He has an enviable reputation for the calibre of his business acumen in the areas of educational institutions, technology based enterprises, franchises and property development companies.\r\n\r\nKevin completed a Bachelor of Economics at the University of Sydney and a Masters of International Business at the University of NSW, and has been actively engaged in business applications for over 20 years.\r\n\r\nKevin’s principal reason in joining TCS was to be part of a growing company that values innovation and fosters new technologies.\r\n\r\n“It is so exciting to be part of an industry that values innovation and thinking outside the box. The expectation from our clients is for us to drive innovation and provide a seamless journey across multi-faceted media. I look forward to facilitating the ongoing introduction of new technologies into Australia through our foreign partners.”', 'Kevin Bae', 'Kevin completed a Bachelor of Economics at the University of Sydney and a Masters of International Business at the University of NSW, and has been actively engaged in business applications for over 20 years. \r\n\r\n\r\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kevin-bae', '', '', '2012-12-18 04:48:41', '2012-12-18 04:48:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=director&#038;p=69', 0, 'director', '', 0),
