(138, 1, '2012-12-18 05:46:19', '2012-12-18 05:46:19', '<span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">Mark Bailey, the CEO of The Creative Shop (TCS), was invited to speak at DIGITAL SIGNAGE WORLD Australia 2012, which was held at Sydney Convention &amp; Exhibition Centre from 20-21 Mar 2012. DIGITAL SIGNAGE WORLD 2012 is Australia''s only dedicated tradeshow and conference for digital signage. This years exhibition featured not only Digital Signage but also other related technologies that extend to Card &amp; Payment Solutions and Near Field Communication (NFC). </span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">Over the two days, Mark presented on the topic ''Creating the visual experience - engaging with the customer through digital display &amp; signage''. </span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">Mark said, "Digital displays and signage as with many digital channels and media is evolving and growing rapidly. We have seen recent applications into Out-of-home (OOH) and other environments, which create a more engaging and impactful consumer experience, which can then be linked to other points of contact to continue and extend the conversation and brand experience in a much more meaningful manner in contrast to passive advertising alone" </span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">Attendees also had the opportunity to view a variety of real world case studies delivered by The Creative Shop on behalf of brands such as G2 Water, Commonwealth Bank of Australia (CBA), V Energy, Pure Blonde and Nokia, demonstrating the effectiveness and success of bringing interactivity and engagement to the consumer. Mark predicted that we will see a continuation in rapid expansion of digital touch-points and implementation methods over the next few years, delivering significant new opportunities to improve marketing ROI and brand engagement. TCS is planning to provide more insights and share learning''s on how companies and brands can improve their own Digital Marketing Strategies, at related conference and seminars throughout 2012. </span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">Written by Ryan Song</span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">From: The Creative Shop</span>', 'MARK BAILEY (CEO OF TCS) PRESENTED AT DIGITAL SIGNAGE WORLD 2012', 'Mark Bailey, the CEO of The Creative Shop (TCS), was invited to speak at DIGITAL SIGNAGE WORLD Australia 2012, which was held at Sydney Convention & Exhibition Centre from 20-21 Mar 2012', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mark-bailey-ceo-of-tcs-presented-at-digital-signage-world-2012', '', '', '2012-12-18 06:13:42', '2012-12-18 06:13:42', '', 0, 'http://192.168.204.156/wordpress/?post_type=news&#038;p=138', 0, 'news', '', 0),
