(140, 1, '2012-12-18 05:48:49', '2012-12-18 05:48:49', '<span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">TCS CEO Mark Bailey today announced that TCS had began working in a new partnership with Fisher &amp; Paykel .</span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">After discussions and submissions over some months focusing on digital marketing solutions for Fisher &amp; Paykel, TCS are proud to be working with this leading Brand name on what we hope will be the first of many interesting and exciting projects.</span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">We will be delivering the first in a potential range of digital and interactive solutions to enable consumers to be better informed and create an interactive experience in various mediums and channels to fully understand the range of products, features and benefits.</span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">This will launch in its first iteration as part of The Food &amp; Wine Shows starting in Melbourne in June 2012 and travelling around the nation over the following months. TCS will be creating an interactive content experience for interactive kiosks and ipad to meet these objectives. The initial focus is around Luxury Spacious Kitchen, Apartment /Limited Space, Outdoor Entertaining, Laundry and the appropriate products for these situations.</span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">Mr Bailey said that TCS are very proud to working with such a leading brand as Fisher &amp; Paykel and thank them for choosing TCS. We look forward to leading the market with some innovative digital and interactive solutions that help raise the marketing and sales efforts of brands like Fisher &amp; Paykel.</span><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><br style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;" /><span style="color: #252525; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: #ffffff;">We very much see that digital can enhance and build on the success of other traditional media and mediums augmenting the consumer experience and engagement opportunity by bringing convenience and access to content and information in new ways that helps continue to provide brands like Fisher &amp; Paykel with a competitive advantage.</span>', 'TCS WORKING WITH LEADING CONSUMER DURABLES BRAND', 'TCS CEO Mark Bailey today announced that TCS had began working in a new partnership with Fisher & Paykel .', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tcs-working-with-leading-consumer-durables-brand', '', '', '2012-12-18 06:13:12', '2012-12-18 06:13:12', '', 0, 'http://192.168.204.156/wordpress/?post_type=news&#038;p=140', 0, 'news', '', 0),
